data.name: CommandButton
desc: specifies the control model for a clickable button which is part of a form component hierarchy.

properties.name: ButtonType
desc: describes the action to be executed by the button when pressed.

properties.name: DefaultState
desc: specifies the default toggle state for the button, used when it is reset.
This property is meaningful only when com.sun.star.awt.UnoControlButtonModel.Toggle is TRUE. In this case, the DefaultState controls to which State the button will be reset.
For a given implementation of the interface, if this (optional) property is present, then also the optional interface com.sun.star.form.XReset must be present.

properties.name: TargetFrame
desc: describes the frame, where to open the document specified by the TargetURL.
This property is evaluated if the button is of type URL.
As always, there is a number of target names which have a special meaning, and force a special com.sun.star.frame.Frame to be used.

properties.name: TargetURL
desc: specifies the URL, which should be opened if the button was clicked.
This property is evaluated if the button is of type URL.
